caption: Photo shared by Tim - Shmee on August 20, 2021 tagging @philwilson, @shmee150wastaken, and @bannedauto. May be an image of 1 person and car.
text: Back at the wheel of an SF90! author: shmee150
caption: Photo shared by Tim - Shmee on August 08, 2021 tagging @mercedesamg, and @theshmeemobiles. May be an image of car.
text: It's time! @theshmeemobiles AMG GT Black Series is being resprayed AMG Solarbeam Yellow, and I cannot wait to see how it looks. This was always the plan hence the choice of Graphite Grey Magno for the base as it's the easiest to work with. The transformation is being done by @chartwell_derby just as per my SLS BS respray to Mystic Blue and the repairs to my Senna before. Why not just order it like this you say? It wasn't an option, and believe me I tried. It was absolutely impossible to order the car (RHD UK allocation) in anything other than the standard 8 choices available so this is the only way. What about the value? Life is too short, I'm going to do many thousands of miles in this car for many years to come, reselling it is not in the plans. #Mercedes #AMG #GTBlackSeries #Shmeemobile #Shmee150

author: thesmokingtire
caption: Photo by Matt Farah on August 19, 2021.
text: When I posted a shot of the Bronco‚Äôs open tailgate before asking if maybe it didn‚Äôt take up too much space, there was a bunch of ‚Äúdurrr but Jeep tho.‚Äù Comments. Making sure I wasn‚Äôt crazy, I found a Wrangler and measured. A Wrangler‚Äôs tailgate is 42 inches across. This is 50.5. If you don‚Äôt think eight inches of difference is a lot when measuring cars, it‚Äôs enough for most manufacturers to use nomenclature like ‚ÄúLWB.‚Äù In this photo, the Bronco is parked four feet from my garage door and the tailgate made impact when opened. I am digging the Bronco so far, but this is pretty poor design for usability, especially considering the pressurized hydraulics open it all the way (like a vertical tailgate). And all you ‚ÄúDurr Jeep‚Äù people can mind your P‚Äôs and fuckin Q‚Äôs because spidey sense was right: massively bigger than a Jeep.
